uk.ac.ed.csbe.sbsivisual.sbsiDataFormat
Class HeaderColumn

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ed.csbe.sbsivisual.sbsiDataFormat.HeaderColumn

public final class HeaderColumn
extends java.lang.Object

Encapsulation of column section of data header file.
Objects of this class are immutable.
Equality is based on the result of getColName().

Author:
Richard Adams

Method Detail

canCreate

public static boolean canCreate(java.lang.String name,
                                java.lang.String units,
                                java.lang.String description)
Tests if name/value annotaion elements can create a syntactically valid HeaderColumn element. External clients constructing these objects should use the following idiom:
   if HeaderColumn.canCreate(name, value) {
     HeaderColumn = HeaderColumn.createHeaderColumn(name, value);
in order to ensure that column elements are constructed according to syntax rules.

Parameters:
name - A candidate col name
units - A candidate col units
description - A candidate description
Returns:
true if a valid HeaderColumn can be created from these parameters.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - for any null parameters.
